Set up your project:

Make sure you have Node.js installed on your machine. If not, you can download it from nodejs.org.
Create a new folder for your project and navigate to it using the terminal or command prompt.
Install dependencies:

Run the following command in the terminal or command prompt to install the required packages:
bash
Copy code
npm install express axios
Get your OpenAI API key:

Replace the placeholder for API_KEY in your code with your actual OpenAI API key.
Run your server:

Start your server by running the following command in the terminal or command prompt:
bash
Copy code
node app.js


Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000 (or the port you specified in your code).
Use your application:

Fill out the form on the webpage and click the "Get Project Score" button.
Check the console or terminal where your server is running to see any logs or errors.
